# Netlify redirects file
# Handle URL redirects and rewrites

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CANONICAL CLEAN URLS (added 2026-06-22)
# Google indexed clean slugs (no .html). Some slugs differ from the filename,
# so they were 404ing (served homepage via the /* fallback). These rules:
#   1) serve each clean slug from its real file (200 rewrite)
#   2) force-redirect the .html version to the clean slug (301!) to kill dupes
# Canonical form = NO trailing slash (Netlify's native pretty-URL form).
# The "!" force flag is REQUIRED to redirect away from a path where a real
# file exists, otherwise Netlify serves the file and ignores the rule.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# 1. Low-cost healthcare  (file: healthcare.html)
/low-cost-hospital        /healthcare.html              200
/low-cost-hospital/       /healthcare.html              200
/healthcare.html          /low-cost-hospital            301!
/healthcare               /low-cost-hospital            301!

# 2. Kids nurseries / education  (file: kids-education.html)
